SYLLABUS:
01. Concepts of epidemiology, hygiene and preventive medicine:
   - Hygiene and epidemiology, definitions, history;
   - basic terminology;
   - the relationship between the environment and human health.
   02. Influence of selected environmental factors on health:
   - burden, environmental factors;
   - air;
   - water.
   03. Nutrition and its impact on health - proteins, fats, cholesterol, margarines, carbohydrates, fiber, energy value of food, recommended nutritional doses, alcohol, foreign substances.
   04. Work and health:
   - risk analysis at work;
   - workplace, work place, work activity;
   - categorization of works;
   - principles of prevention;
   - workload burdens.
   05. Basics of hygiene of children and adolescents:
   - growth and development of children;
   - the risk of harm to the health of the child;
   - prevention of child injuries, violence against children;
   - addiction issues in adolescents, behavioral disorders, sexually transmitted diseases.
   06. Principles of hygiene of operation of individual types of workplaces, hand hygiene, anti-epidemic regime.
   07. Physical activity as a basic factor of lifestyle:
   - supporting physical activity (global, European and national strategies);
   - importance of optimal physical activity for prevention of non-infectious diseases;
   - possibilities of evaluation of physical activity.
   08. Prevention of non-infectious diseases of mass incidence:
   - obesity, epidemiology, prevention, treatment;
   - cardiovascular disease, risk factors, prevention;
   - oncological diseases and their primary prevention.
   09. Epidemiology of infectious diseases:
   - the process of spreading the disease;
   - epidemiological measures;
   - nosocomial infections;
   - disinfection and sterilization.
   10. Epidemiology of cardiovascular diseases
   11. Epidemiology of oncological diseases

LEARNING_OUTCOMES:
Upon successful completion of the course "Sports Training" will be able to:
   - interpret sports training bases;
   - define basic concepts of conditioning and sports training;
   - define basic forms and methods used in sports training;
   - apply various methods, and forms of development of physical abilities in practice;
   - describe the basic principles and the effects of strength, endurance, speed training and coordination skills training in the context of individual and team sports.

SYLLABUS:
Lecture:
   01. Introduction to Rehabilitation:
   Definition, history, education, qualifications and competences in the field, means of physiotherapy;
   - organization of rehabilitation and physiotherapeutic care, competences of individual team members;
   - definition of quality in healthcare, healthcare standards;
   - quality management of healthcare provided and patient safety, quality management models and their relationships;
   - professional competences and training opportunities for physiotherapists;
   - the role of medical history in rehabilitation;
   - establishing a short and long term plan;
   - indications and contraindications to physiotherapy in general.
   02. Kinesiotherapy I:
   - passive and active therapy;
   - positioning;
   - a vertical-locomotion plan.
   03. Kinesiotherapy II:
   - fitness therapy,
   - fundamentals of pulmonary rehabilitation and respiratory physiotherapy.
   04. Rehabilitation treatment
   05. Physiotherapy in preventive care, in acute care, in chronic diseases.
   06. International Classification of Functioning, Disability and Health (ICF). Principles of physiotherapist work based on "evidence-based medicine" (EBM).

   Exercises:
   01. Physiotherapist approach to patient, medical history.
   02. Motor learning - types of motor learning and their use in patient education. Individual and group therapy.
   03. Patient mobilization - passive movement (use of passive kinesiotherapy in   rehabilitation)
   04. Patient mobilization:
   - assisted movement (use of kinesiotherapy with assistance in rehabilitation);
   - active movement (use of active kinesiotherapy in rehabilitation);
   - fitness therapy;
   - individual and group therapy.
   05. Rehabilitation nursing - positioning (indications, principles, goals and ways of positioning)
   06. Verticalization-locomotion plan
   07. Introduction to pulmonary rehabilitation - basics and techniques of respiratory physiotherapy
   08. Analytical methods of kinesiotherapy for muscle imbalance compensation - muscle relaxation, stretching.
   09. Analytical methods of kinesiotherapy for compensation of muscle imbalances - muscle facilitation, strengthening.

LEARNING_OUTCOMES:
Students will be able to:
   - identify and summarize important features of the physiotherapy field and explain its importance in prevention and specific therapy;
   - identify and describe current domestic and foreign trends in physiotherapy;
   - practically apply rehabilitation nursing procedures and basic therapeutic techniques; - describe the basic division of physiotherapy;
   - orientate between basic concepts and rehabilitation approaches and basic therapeutic techniques.

