SYLLABUS:
1. Introduction to Strategic Management- the necessity of strategic and financial planning, basic strategic management concepts and models in the global sports industry;
   2. Strategic environment: Market environment, PESTEL analysis, Porter's five forces model,sporting market models and their strategic implications, the concentration of capital and market niches in sport;
   3. The role of the state in the development of the sport - the reasons for government intervention, regulation control, the extent of state intervention;
   4. The non-profit sector and sport - the role of the nonprofit sector in sport , organizations in the nonprofit sector for the sport.
   5. Professional sport - the concept, the role of media, management of athletes, evaluation of results;
   6. The principles of strategic management and strategic choice in sports - the basis of competitive advantage, strategy, diversification, value chain analysis, SWOT / TOWS matrix analysis and RACES;
   7. Organizational and strategic changes – conditions of internal organization in sports, archetypes of the dynamics of changes in the internal organization of sports organizations for the implementation of the chosen strategy;
   8. Human resources management in sport – specifics of the management and evaluation of human resources in sport organizations;
   9. Leadership - Leadership Theory, differences between manager and leader and their implications in the management of sports organizations;
   10. Organizational culture in sports - specifics and importance of organizational culture in sport, subculture, organizational identity, diagnosis and management of changes in the organizational culture of sport organizations;
   11. Financial management of sports organizations - financial resources in sport, information for financial management and their importance to the management of sports organizations;
   12. Strategy Implementation - from the perspective of the marketing, organization and financial management;
   13. Performance evaluation in sport – specifics of the performance evaluation in sports organization, multidimensional approach to performance evaluation and its criteria

OBJECTIVES:
After the successful completion of the course, students will be able to:
   1. understand the different models of the processes of strategic management of sports organizations and discuss the relevance of these models, taking into account the specifics of the sport;
   2. critically analyze the key features of the current strategic management in the sports environment;
   3. identify strategic decisions of managers in sport organizations
   4. critically evaluate strategic options of sports organizations, including their feasibility and sustainability;
   5. identify problems and opportunities the sports organizations are facing when implementing their chosen strategies

LEARNING_OUTCOMES:
After completing the course student will be able to:
   - characterize the specifics of sports nutrition;
